                         AN IMPLEMENTATION OF
                  MAXIMALLY STABLE EXTREMAL REGIONS

                            Andrea Vedaldi
                         vedaldi@cs.ucla.edu
                   http://vision.ucla.edu/~vedaldi/

This is a MATLAB/C implementation of Maximally Stable Extremal Regions
(MSER) [1] similar to [2]. See the documentation in 'doc/' to get started.

COMPLING
  From MATLAB prompt
  > mser_compile
  From shell prompt (Linux, Mac OS X)
  > make

TESTING
  Demo code requires the VLUtil package
  (http://vision.ucla.edu/code/vlutil/vutil.html)

  > mser_demo
  > mser_demo2
  > mser_demo3
  > mser_demo4

CHANGES

  0.5   Bug fix (thanks to Wafting).
  0.4   Added citatio on 3-D MSERS.
  0.3   Bucket sort and rank union added. Better options handling.
  0.2   Some bug fixes (thank to Q. S. Luo).
  0.1   Initial release.

CREDITS
  [1] J. Matas, O. Chum, M. Urban, and T. Pajdla, 
      "Robust wide baseline stereo from maximally stable extremal regions," 
      in Proc. BMVC, 2002.

